The low l TT power spectrum presented is the posterior on the underlying power spectrum (as opposed to a measured power spectrum), with central points being the posterior maximum. The temperature map presented ia also the posterior maximum, which is why it can include the masked regions.

For polarisation though, they don't appear to take this approach and instead use a masked map and then measure the power spectrum from that, with as far as I can see no correction for the cut sky.

